==English==
===Etymology===
From the surname of the British former prime minister [[w:Margaret Thatcher|Margaret Thatcher]], + '''[[-ite]]'''

===Adjective===
'''Thatcherite'''

#Of or relating to [[Thatcherism]].
#:''a '''Thatcherite''' policy''
#Supporting Thatcherism.
#:''He has a '''Thatcherite''' outlook on life.''

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[thatcheriläinen]] (1,2)

===Noun===
'''Thatcherite''' (''plural'' '''Thatcherites''')

#An [[advocate]] of Thatcherism.

===Related terms===
*[[Thatcherism]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[thatcheriläinen]]

